# Statistics Practice 

## Mean 

### Formula
Mean = Sum of values / Number of values 

#### Questions

- Suppose the marks of 5 students are: 
60, 70, 80, 90, 100 
Mean = (60 + 70 + 80 + 90 + 100) / 5 
Mean = 400 / 5
Mean = 80 

- A company wants to know the average salary of employees. Employee salaries: 
₹30,000, ₹35,000, ₹40,000, ₹45,000, ₹50,000 
Mean = (30,000 + 35,000 + 40,000 + 45,000 + 50,000) / 5
Mean = 200,000 / 5
Mean = 40,000

